nues%20to%20be%20celebrated%20in%20the%20music%20industry%2C%20he%20has%20also%20been%20accused%20of%20assault%20by%20Dee%20Barnes%2C%20a%20journalist%20and%20MC%2C%20who%20told%20Rolling%20Stone%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rollingstone.com%2Fmusic%2Fmusic-news%2Fdr-dre-grammy-award-dee-barnes-reacts-abuse-1234675681%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshe's%20been%20blacklisted%20by%20the%20music%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20speaking%20out%20against%20the%20mogul.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E16.%20'U.N.I.T.Y.'%20by%20Queen%20Latifah%20(1993)%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EQueen%20Latifah%20became%20the%20first%20female%20rapper%20to%20receive%20a%20Grammy%20Award%20in%201995%2C%20winning%20best%20rap%20solo%20performance%20for%20%26quot%3BU.N.I.T.Y.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20with%20many%20of%20her%20signature%20songs%2C%20%26quot%3BU.N.I.T.Y.%26quot%3B%20celebrates%20the%20resilience%20of%20women%20in%20a%20male-dominated%20world%2C%20explicitly%20condemning%20issues%20like%20sexual%20harassment%20(%26quot%3BI%20walked%20past%20these%20dudes%20when%20they%20passed%20me%20%2F%20One%20of%20'em%20felt%20my%20booty%2C%20he%20was%20nasty%26quot%3B)%20and%20sexist%20language%20in%20her%20own%20industry%20(%26quot%3BInstinct%20leads%20me%20to%20another%20flow%20%2F%20Every%20time%20I%20hear%20a%20brother%20call%20a%20girl%20a%20bitch%20or%20a%20ho%20%2F%20Tryna%20make%20a%20sister%20feel%20low%20%2F%20You%20know%20all%20of%20that%20gots%20to%20go%26quot%3B).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20this%20year%2C%20Latifah%20made%20history%20again%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2023%2F04%2F12%2F1169227901%2Fnational-recording-registry%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20first%20female%20rapper%20to%20join%20the%20National%20Recording%20Registry%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20induction%20of%20her%20debut%20album%20%26quot%3BAll%20Hail%20The%20Queen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E17.%20'None%20of%20Your%20Business'%20by%20Salt-N-Pepa%20(1994)%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.grammy.com%2Fawards%2F37th-annual-grammy-awards%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E37th%20annual%20Grammys%3C%2Fa%3E%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20historic%20night%20for%20women%20in%20hip-hop.%20After%20Queen%20Latifah%20accepted%20the%20award%20for%20best%20rap%20solo%20performance%2C%20Salt-N-Pepa%20became%20the%20first-ever%20female%20rap%20group%20to%20take%20home%20a%20golden%20gramophone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECheryl%20James%20(aka%20Salt)%2C%20Sandra%20Denton%20(aka%20Pepa)%2C%20and%20Deidra%20Roper%20(aka%20DJ%20Spinderella)%20won%20best%20rap%20performance%20by%20a%20duo%20or%20group%20for%20%26quot%3BNone%20of%20Your%20Business%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20sex-positive%20anthem%20that%20calls%20out%20misogynistic%20double%20standards.%20It%20was%20their%20third%20nomination%20in%20the%20category%20that%20had%20previously%20been%20dominated%20by%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20song's%20parent%20album%2C%20%26quot%3BVery%20Necessary%2C%26quot%3B%20was%20eventually%20certified%20multiplatinum%20%E2%80%94%20making%20Salt-N-Pepa%20the%20first%20female%20rap%20group%20to%20achieve%20the%20feat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222623%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Salt-n-Pepa%20grammys%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656638ccc58b6f84123b09d6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221967%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESalt-n-Pepa%20at%20the%201995%20Grammy%20Awards.%3Cp%3ERon%20Galella%2C%20Ltd.%2FRon%20Galella%20Collection%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E18.%20'Gangsta's%20Paradise'%20by%20Coolio%20featuring%20L.V.%20(1995)%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGangsta's%20Paradise%26quot%3B%20didn't%20just%20spark%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.billboard.com%2Fmusic%2Fchart-beat%2Fcoolio-gangstas-paradise-forever-number-one-1235149707%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%