%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJim%20and%20Ellen%20Diamond%20left%20their%20four-bedroom%20house%20in%20the%20suburbs%20for%20a%20one-bedroom%20unit%20in%20NYC.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELiving%20in%20the%20city%20makes%20life%20more%20convenient%2C%20as%20they%20no%20longer%20have%20to%20drive%20or%20maintain%20a%20home.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EActivities%2C%20like%20visiting%20Carnegie%20Hall%2C%20are%20more%20accessible%20plus%20their%20doctors%20are%20closer%20now%2C%20too.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Jim%20and%20Ellen%20Diamond%2C%20both%2088.%20The%20Diamonds%20moved%20in%20February%202023%20from%20Hastings-on-Hudson%2C%20New%20York%20%E2%80%94%20about%2023%20miles%20north%20of%20Midtown%2C%20Manhattan%20%E2%80%94%20to%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcoterieseniorliving.com%2Fluxury-retirement-communities%2Fcoterie-hudson-yards-new-york-ny%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ECoterie%20Hudson%20Yards%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%20luxury%20senior-%20and%20assisted-living%20facility%20in%20Manhattan%2C%20where%20one-bedrooms%20like%20the%20Diamonds'%20rent%20from%20%2416%2C800%20a%20month.%20The%20conversation%20was%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJim%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20When%20we%20first%20moved%20in%20to%20the%20suburbs%2C%20we%20were%20the%20same%20age%20as%20everybody%20else%2C%20more%20or%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEllen%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20mean%2C%20you'd%20like%20to%20stay%2032-years-old%20forever%2C%20but%20you%20don't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJim%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20neighbors%20were%20getting%20too%20young%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEllen%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20weren't%20getting%20old.%20They%20were%20getting%20young.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJim%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20were%20there%20for%2050%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEllen%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20lot%20of%20our%20friends%20in%20Hastings%20have%20moved%20to%20senior%20residences%20in%20other%20cities.%20I%20don't%20know%20any%20of%20our%20friends%20who've%20moved%20to%20the%20city.%20Maybe%20it's%20because%20it's%20more%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20we%20decided%20to%20move%20to%20the%20city%20was%20we%20needed%20more%20help%20as%20we%20were%20getting%20older.%20And%20mainly%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20you%20should%20be%20driving%20after%20the%20age%20of%20200-something%2C%20and%20you%20absolutely%20needed%20a%20car%20in%20the%20suburbs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJim%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20had%20real%20motivation%20to%20change%20our%20scenario.%20We%20had%20to%20do%20all%20our%20own%20shopping%2C%20we%20had%20to%20have%20a%20car%20to%20do%20that%2C%20and%20we%20had%20to%20fix%20the%20car%20and%20all%20that%20stuff%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20even%20painted%20the%20house%20twice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20wanted%20to%20be%20closer%20to%20our%20favorite%20activities%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEllen%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20city%20is%20stimulating%2C%20and%20one%20of%20the%20antidotes%20to%20old%20age%20is%20keeping%20up%20your%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJim%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20You%20can%20do%20things%20here.%20I've%20seen%20places%20where%20they%20had%20retirement%20areas%20where%20people%20were%20sitting%20on%20the%20porch%20all%20grouped%20in%20a%20circle%20looking%20out%20in%20the%20distance.%20And%20that%20got%20to%20me.%20That%20might%20be%20good%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20days%2C%20but%20I%20wouldn't%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEllen%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWe%20wanted%20to%20be%20in%20this%20city%2C%20really%2C%20because%20of%20Carnegie%20Hall.%20And%20doctors.%20All%20our%20doctors%20were%20in%20New%20York%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJim%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20Hastings%2C%20we%20didn't%20neglect%20coming%20into%20New%20York%20City.%20We%20went%20to%20classical%20music%20concerts%20all%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEllen%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20couple%20or%20three%20times%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222119%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20large%20brick%20building%20on%20a%20corner%20in%20NYC.%20(Carnegie%20Hall)%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657c7f8f0ec98e92f74ffa08%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Diamonds%20often%20traveled%20into%20New%20York%20City%20to%20see%20classical%20music%20shows%20at%20Carnegie%20Hall.%20Living%20in%20the%20city%2C%20and%20closer%20to%20the%20venue%2C%20is%20a%20huge%20perk%20for%20them.%3Cp%3Edemerzel21%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJim%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWe%20took%20the%20train%2C%20we%20drove%20and%20parked%20%E2%80%94%20anything%20necessary%20to%20get%20into%20Manhattan%20to%20go%20to%20all%20those%20wonderful%20things.%20Museums%2C%20too.%20All%20the%20things%20that%20New%20York%20City%20offers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoving%20saved%20us%20the%20time%20we%20spent%20driving%20back%20and%20forth%20to%20the%20city%20or%20taking%20the%20trains%2C%20which%20began%20to%20toll%20on%20us%20as%20we%20got%20older.%20And%20we%20knew%20that%20the%20future%20had%20this%20plan%20for%20us%20to%20have%20a%20place%20where%20there%20was%20some%20help%2C%20but%20we%20needed%20it%20later%20on.%20We're%20still%20mobile%2C%20and%20it%20seems%20to%20be%20working%20out%20very%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlanning%20dinners%2C%20shopping%2C%20all%20that%20got%20eliminated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEllen%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20lifestyle%20is%20entirely%20different.%20And%20that's%20not%20necessarily%20bad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EOur%20home%20is%20significantly%20smaller%20than%20in%20the%20suburbs%2C%20but%20errands%20are%20easier%20to%20run%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEllen%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Before%20Coterie%20was%20built%2C%20we%20were%20looking%20fairly%20seriously%20in%20another%2C%20somewhat%20similar%20place%2C%20but%20our%20grand%20piano%20wouldn't%20fit.%20That%20was%20a%20major%20factor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJim%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20piano%20goes%20or%20I%20don't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEllen%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20were%20worried%20about%20it%2C%20but%20Steinway%20won't%20move%20a%20piano%20until%20they%20send%20somebody%20to%20inspect%20the%20place%20it's%20going.%20And%20Steinway%20did%20and%20it%20was%20fine.%20But%20we%20didn't%20watch%20them%20crane%20it%20up%20the%20side%20of%20the%20building%2C%20that%20would%20not%20have%20been%20comforting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20apartments%20are%20bigger%20here.%20I%20wouldn't%20say%20they%20were%20enormous%2C%20but%20they%20were%20big%20enough%20for%20the%20stupid%20grand%20piano.%20It%20doesn't%20fit%2C%20but%20it's%20in%20there%20anyway%2C%20you%20could%20walk%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20house%20we%20had%20in%20Hastings%20had%20small%20rooms%2C%20but%20there%20were%20four%20bedrooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224338%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Grand%20Central%20Station%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F518fc9c76bb3f7521f000001%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222872%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGrand%20Central%20Station%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FEric%20Thayer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20one-bedroom%20and%20the%20rooms%20aren't%20large.%20There's%20one%20smallish%20bedroom%20and%20a%20smallish%20living%20room%2C%20just%20big%20enough%20for%20the%20piano%20and%20not%20a%20whole%20lot%20else.%20And%20that's%20the%20way%20it%20is.%20We%20had%20to%20throw%20out%20mountains%20of%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20least%20expensive%20unit%20on%20the%20lowest%20floor.%20It%20is%20expensive%20here.%20There's%20no%20getting%20around%20it.%20A%20place%20like%20this%20with%20all%20the%20personal%20amenities%2C%20the%20care%20that's%20given%20and%20the%20expertise%20and%20the%20staff%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJim%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Being%20here%20has%20eliminated%20a%20lot%20of%20tasks%2C%20like%20having%20a%20car%20and%20having%20it%20repaired%2C%20and%20other%20things%20like%20that.%20There%20are%20a%20few%20stores%20we%20can%20walk%20to%20and%20get%20groceries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEllen%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20run%20errands%20to%20the%20drugstore.%20We%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20last%20Friday%20doing%20errands%20in%20Grand%20Central%20Station.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20say%20it%20has%20gone%20far%20beyond%20what%20we%20expected.%20The%20instant%20we%20did%20move%20in%2C%20we%20realized%20what%20a%20good%20choice%20it%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-new-york-assisted-living-carnegie-hall-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702726681000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657cc6880ec98e92f750340e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-new-york-assisted-living-carnegie-hall-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jim%20and%20Ellen%20Diamond%20left%20the%20suburbs%20in%20their%20old%20age.%20Now%20their%20doctors%20are%20closer%20and%20they%20can%20visit%20their%20favorite%20place%2C%20Carnegie%20Hall.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jpandy%40insider.com%20(Jordan%20Pandy)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-new-york-assisted-living-carnegie-hall-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mahesh%20Kumawat%2C%206th%20Parliament%20Breach%20Accused%2C%20Sent%20To%207-Day%20Cop%20Custody%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDelhi%20police%20today%20made%20the%20sixth%20arrest%20in%20the%20Parliament%20security%20breach%20case%20where%20two%20men%20jumped%20into%20the%20House%20and%20released%20coloured%20smoke.%20Mahesh%20Kumawat%20was%20taken%20into%20custody%20today%20for%20allegedly%20helping%20the%20'mastermind'%20Lalit%20Jha%20escape%20from%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahesh%20Kumawat%20had%20come%20on%20his%20own%20to%20a%20police%20station%20along%20with%20Lalit%20Jha%20Thursday%20night%20and%20both%20were%20handed%20over%20to%20the%20Special%20Cell%2C%20the%20officer%20said.%20He%20was%20being%20interrogated%20since%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20a%20member%20of%20the%20now%20deleted%20Bhagat%20Singh%20Fan%20Club%20page%20created%20by%20the%20accused.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKumawat%20has%20been%20arrested%20on%20charges%20of%20destruction%20of%20evidence%20and%20criminal%20conspiracy%2C%20police%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20been%20sent%20to%207-day%20police%20custody.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20said%20police%20are%20likely%20to%20seek%20the%20Parliament's%20permission%20to%20recreate%20the%20December%2013%20incident%20that%20unfolded%20on%20the%20anniversary%20of%20the%202001%20attack%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolice%20are%20also%20questioning%20Lalit%20Jha%2C%20who%20they%20believe%20is%20the%20'mastermind'%20behind%20the%20breach.%20Jha%2C%20who%20hails%20from%20West%20Bengal%2C%20was%20sent%20to%20seven-day%20police%20custody%20on%20Friday%20after%20his%20arrest%20last%20night.%20Police%20claimed%20in%20the%20Patiala%20House%20court%20that%20he%20admitted%20that%20the%20accused%20met%20many%20times%20to%20hatch%20the%20conspiracy%20to%20breach%20Parliament%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20he%20was%20also%20required%20to%20be%20interrogated%20to%20ascertain%20whether%20the%20accused%20had%20association%20with%20any%20enemy%20country%20or%20terrorist%20organisation%2C%20police%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702726560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fkj8d3gkc_mahesh-kumawat_625x300_16_December_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmahesh-kumawat-6th-accused-in-parliament-security-breach-arrested-4684771%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Delhi%20police%20today%20made%20the%20sixth%20arrest%20in%20the%20Parliament%20security%20breach%20case%20where%20two%20men%20jumped%20into%20the%20House%20and%20released%20coloured%20smoke.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmahesh-kumawat-6th-accused-in-parliament-security-breach-arrested-4684771%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmahesh-kumawat-6th-accused-in-parliament-security-breach-arrested-4684771%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmahesh-kumawat-6th-accused-in-parliament-security-breach-arrested-4684771%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22HENRYs%20are%20turning%20to%20a%20little-known%20and%20risky%20type%20of%20mortgage%20as%20home%20prices%20soar%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20FOR%20SALE%20sign%20is%20displayed%20outside%20a%20property%20on%20Madison%20Ave.%20in%20Toronto.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657c74ff7a3c8094d5dd7d15%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22854%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EInterest-only%20mortgages%20were%20much%20more%20strictly%20regulated%20after%20the%20financial%20crisis%2C%20but%20now%20higher-income%20borrowers%20are%20turning%20to%20them%20as%20home%20prices%20stay%20high.%3Cp%3ELance%20McMillan%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20Americans%20who%20are%20high%20earners%2C%20but%20not%20rich%20yet%20are%20opting%20for%20non-traditional%20mortgages.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EInterest-only%20mortgages%20offer%20lower%20monthly%20payments%2C%20at%20least%20initially%2C%20but%20can%20be%20risky.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey're%20best%20suited%20for%20buyers%20of%20higher-end%20property%20who%20invest%20their%20money%20elsewhere.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20home%20prices%20and%20mortgage%20rates%20sky%20high%2C%20potential%20homeowners%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0even%20those%20with%20deep%20pockets%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0are%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20ease%20the%20cost%20burden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Americans%20who%20are%20high%20earners%2C%20but%20not%20rich%20yet%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhenry-student-loans-six-figure-income-millennial-gen-z-retirement-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eknown%20as%20HENRYs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20are%20opting%20for%20unusual%20interest-only%20mortgages%20that%20boost%20affordability%2C%20at%20least%20in%20the%20short-term.%20These%20loans%20allow%20the%20borrower%20to%20pay%20just%20interest%20and%20none%20of%20the%20principal%20for%20a%20certain%20number%20of%20years.%20The%20loans%20are%20generally%20reserved%20for%20more%20affluent%20buyers%20of%20higher-end%20property%20who%20can%20afford%20a%20sizeable%20down%20payment%20and%20have%20sufficient%20money%20saved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20attractive%20benefits%20of%20this%20kind%20of%20loan.%20They%20offer%20lower%20monthly%20payments%20at%20first%2C%20which%20allow%20borrowers%20to%20invest%20the%20money%20they%20would%20otherwise%20spend%20to%20pay%20off%20their%20house%20on%20other%2C%20higher-return%20investments.%20They%20also%20allow%20borrowers%20whose%20incomes%20are%20expected%20to%20rise%20in%20the%20future%20to%20buy%20more%20expensive%20homes%20than%20they%20otherwise%20would%20be%20able%20to%20afford.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20higher%20risks%20than%20a%20conventional%20mortgage.%20Borrowers%20won't%20gain%20equity%20in%20their%20home%2C%20beyond%20the%20down%20payment%20they%20made.%20They're%20on%20the%20hook%20for%20potentially%20higher%20mortgage%20payments%20in%20the%20future%2C%20and%20if%20their%20home%20value%20declines%2C%20they%20could%20lose%20the%20equity%20they%20have%20or%20the%20ability%20to%20refinance.%20Some%20interest-only%20loans%20require%20borrowers%20to%20pay%20off%20the%20entirety%20of%20the%20principal%20once%20the%20interest-only%20period%20ends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Sam%20McNerney%20and%20his%20wife%20were%20looking%20to%20buy%20a%20home%20in%20Brooklyn%20in%20the%20spring%20of%202022%2C%20the%20homes%20they%20liked%20largely%20exceeded%20their%20budget%2C%20which%20was%20between%20%242%E2%80%93%242.5%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20one%20day%20they%20got%20an%20unexpected%20opportunity.%20Their%20neighbors%20directly%20across%20the%20street%20from%20their%20rental%20apartment%20in%20Carroll%20Gardens%20were%20about%20to%20put%20their%20three-bedroom%20brownstone%20on%20the%20market.%20The%20house%20was%20exactly%20what%20they%20were%20looking%20for%2C%20except%20it%20was%20priced%20at%20%243.1%20million.%20But%20their%20neighbors%20offered%20to%20sell%20it%20to%20them%20before%20putting%20it%20on%20the%20market.%20Without%20broker's%20fees%2C%20the%20home%20would%20cost%20about%20%242.8%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcNerney%2C%20a%20self-employed%20marketing%20consultant%2C%20was%20initially%20concerned%20the%20house%20was%20just%20too%20risky%20and%20expensive%20of%20a%20purchase.%20The%20future%20of%20New%20York%20City%20real%20estate%20was%20still%20somewhat%20unclear%20as%20many%20who%20fled%20the%20city%20when%20the%20pandemic%20hit%20were%20slow%20to%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20First%20Republic%20bank%20offered%20him%20and%20his%20wife%20a%2040-year%20interest-only%20loan%2C%20they%20sprung%20for%20it.%20They%20paid%20a%2020%25%20down%20payment%20and%20locked%20in%20a%20low%20mortgage%20rate%20of%20between%202.6%20and%202.7%25%20for%20the%20first%2010%20years%20of%20the%20loan%2C%20and%20a%20guarantee%20that%20their%20rate%20would%20double%20at%20that%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20monthly%2C%20interest-only%20mortgage%20payment%20is%20just%20under%20%245%2C000%20per%20month%2C%20which%20is%20just%20a%20few%20hundred%20dollars%20more%20than%20they%20were%20previously%20spending%20on%20rent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEighteen%20months%20later%2C%20McNerney%20is%20still%20happy%20with%20their%20decision.%20They%20can%20easily%20afford%20their%20payments%20now%2C%20are%20saving%20up%20for%20the%20future%20rate-hike%2C%20and%20Brooklyn%20real%20estate%20is%20booming.%20The%20couple%20thinks%20they'll%20be%20in%20the%20house%20for%20fifteen%20or%20twenty%20years%2C%20at%20which%20point%20their%20kids%20will%20be%20through%20high%20school%20and%20they%20might%20downsize%20or%20leave%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20days%2C%20it%20seems%20like%20a%20pretty%20safe%20bet%20that%20in%2010%20to%2020%20years%20from%20now%2C%20the%20value%20will%20be%20higher%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20if%20it's%20going%20to%20skyrocket%20or%20be%20a%20little%20bit%20higher%2C%20but%20we%20don't%20think%20it'll%20go%20down.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20deal%20for%20'sophisticated%20investors'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMcNerney%20and%20his%20wife%20are%20the%20target%20demographic%20suitable%20for%20an%20interest-only%20loan.%20But%20these%20mortgages%20can%20be%20very%20risky%20if%20a%20borrower%20doesn't%20have%20sufficient%20funds%20to%20handle%20higher%20payments%20down%20the%20line%2C%20or%20the%20property%20loses%20value%2C%20in%20which%20case%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3Eborrowers%20have%20to%20be%20prepared%20for%20potentially%20higher%20interest%20rates%20after%20the%20initial%20stage%20of%20their%20loan%20is%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20loans%20are%20a%20%26quot%3Bniche%20product%26quot%3B%20that%20should%20be%20reserved%20for%20high-end%20real%20estate%20purchases%20by%20borrowers%20who%20are%20%26quot%3Bsophisticated%20investors%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Chen%20Zhao%2C%20the%20head%20of%20economic%20research%20at%20Redfin.%20Since%20you're%20not%20building%20equity%20in%20your%20home%20under%20an%20interest-only%20mortgage%2C%20those%20who%20take%20out%20these%20loans%20should%20be%20investing%20their%20money%20in%20other%20ways%20that%20are%20likely%20to%20give%20them%20a%20better%20return%2C%20Zhao%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20proliferation%20of%20interest-only%20mortgages%20could%20also%20even%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehurt%20buyers%20who%20can't%20afford%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20them.%20Because%20they%20allow%20affluent%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eborrowers%20to%20buy%20more%20expensive%20homes%2C%20they%20can%20help%20inflate%20prices%20in%20already%20high-cost%20markets.%20Claes%20B%C3%A4ckman%2C%20a%20researcher%20at%20the%20Leibniz%20Institute%20for%20Financial%20Research%20SAFE%20in%20Germany%20who%20has%20studied%20the%20introduction%20of%20interest-only%20mortgages%20in%20Denmark%2C%20says%20the%20loan%20type%20doesn't%20significantly%20boost%20affordability%20or%20allow%20more%20young%20people%20to%20become%20homeowners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it%20will%20certainly%20help%20the%20buyers%20who%20can%20afford%20to%20get%20one%20of%20these%2C%20but%20if%20they%20are%20competing%20against%20other%20buyers%20who%20can%20also%20get%20an%20interest-only%20mortgage%2C%20they%20might%20not%20get%20much%20of%20a%20benefit%20in%20terms%20of%20affordability%2C%26quot%3B%20B%C3%A4ckman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Renzo%20Salazar%20maintains%20the%20yard%20around%20a%20foreclosed%20home%20after%20the%20bank%20hired%20him%20to%20keep%20the%20home%20from%20falling%20into%20complete%20dilapidation%20on%20November%2010%2C%202011%20in%20Miami%2C%20Florida.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657c80d60ec98e92f74ffae1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22843%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERenzo%20Salazar%20maintains%20the%20yard%20around%20a%20foreclosed%20home%20after%20the%20bank%20hired%20him%20to%20keep%20the%20home%20from%20falling%20into%20complete%20dilapidation%20on%20November%2010%2C%202011%20in%20Miami%2C%20Florida.%3Cp%3EJoe%20Raedle%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20history%20of%20predatory%20lending%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInterest-only%20mortgages%20were%20much%20more%20common%2C%20especially%20for%20less-affluent%20borrowers%2C%20in%20the%20years%20leading%20up%20to%20the%202008%20financial%20crisis.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20many%20homebuyers%20were%20offered%20risky%20loans%20they%20couldn't%20afford%2C%20which%20ultimately%20led%20to%20the%20subprime%20mortgage%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20financial%20crisis%2C%20the%20federal%20government%20passed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffiles.consumerfinance.gov%2Ff%2F201509_cfpb_readiness-guide_mortgage-implementation.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eregulations%20on%20risky%20mortgages%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20making%20interest-only%20loans%20much%20less%20common.%20But%20with%20home%20prices%20soaring%20and%20interest%20rates%20stubbornly%20high%2C%20buyers%20are%20again%20opting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fbusiness%2Fhomebuyers-seek-riskier-loans-echoes-2008-housing-crisis-rcna51858%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efor%20riskier%20loans%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20interest-only.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHillary%2C%20whose%20last%20name%20is%20known%20to%20Business%20Insider%20but%20requested%20partial%20anonymity%20to%20protect%20her%20husband's%20business%2C%20and%20her%20husband%20were%20victims%20of%20these%20predatory%20lending%20practices.%20In%202007%2C%20the%20couple%20took%20out%20an%20interest-only%20mortgage%20to%20buy%20a%20%24585%2C000%20home%20in%20San%20Diego.%20The%20house%20was%20down%20the%20street%20from%20Hillary's%20mother%3Cstrong%3E%3Cs%3E%20%3C%2Fs%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20the%20couple%20wanted%20it%20to%20be%20their%20forever%20home%2C%20so%20they%20splurged.%20While%20their%20real%20estate%20agent%20warned%20them%20against%20taking%20out%20such%20a%20large%2C%20high-interest%20loan%2C%20the%20bank%20encouraged%20them%20to%20take%20on%20two%20loans%20without%20any%20down%20payment%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0one%20at%208%25%20and%20the%20other%20at%209%25%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20financial%20crisis%20hit%2C%20Hillary's%20husband%2C%20a%20commission-based%20financial%20advisor%2C%20saw%20his%20income%20plummet.%20Hillary%2C%20a%20self-employed%20photographer%2C%20also%20took%20a%20hit.%20Then%20the%20couple%20had%20a%20new%20baby.%20They%20were%20soon%20forced%20to%20take%20out%20loans%20to%20make%20their%20%244%2C000%20monthly%20mortgage%20payments.%20When%20they%20asked%20their%20bank%20to%20modify%20the%20terms%20of%20the%20loan%2C%20it%20refused.%20The%20couple%20declared%20bankruptcy%20and%20ultimately%20sold%20the%20house%20in%202012%20for%20just%20%24365%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%20now%2C%20Hillary%20thinks%20she%20and%20her%20now%20ex-husband%20were%20too%20optimistic%20about%20their%20future%20income%20when%20they%20bought%20the%20house%2C%20but%20that%20her%20bank%20was%20reckless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20clearly%20should%20never%20have%20given%20us%20a%20loan%2C%26quot%3B%20Hillary%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20when%20you're%20young%20and%20it's%20the%2C%20quote%2C%20perfect%20home%20for%20you%2C%20you%20know%2C%20what%20are%20you%20supposed%20to%20do%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20concerned%20that%20some%20buyers%20are%20now%20falling%20into%20a%20similar%20trap%20of%20believing%20they'll%20be%20able%20to%20refinance%20their%20loans%20later%20for%20a%20better%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20broader%20world%20of%20real%20estate%2C%20interest-only%20mortgages%20could%20be%20contributing%20to%20another%20crisis.%20These%20days%2C%20interest-only%20mortgages%20are%20increasingly%20popular%20among%20commercial%20real%20estate%20buyers.%20They%20made%20up%2088%25%20of%20new%20commercial%20mortgage-backed%20issuances%20in%202021%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0an%20increase%20from%2051%25%20in%202013%2C%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Finterest-only-loans-helped-commercial-property-boom-now-theyre-coming-due-c3754941%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20based%20on%20data%20from%20the%20company%20Trepp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it's%20not%20going%20well%20for%20borrowers.%20Commercial%20mortgage%20defaults%20are%20on%20the%20rise.%20With%20interest%20rates%20so%20high%2C%20many%20office%20building%20owners%20aren't%20able%20to%20secure%20new%20loans%20they%20can%20afford.%20In%20May%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fitchratings.com%2Fresearch%2Fstructured-finance%2Fupdated-scenarios-show-fewer-maturing-us-cmbs-loans-able-to-refinance-03-05-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EFitch%20Ratings%20estimated%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%2035%25%20of%20pooled%20securitized%20commercial%20mortgages%20due%20between%20April%20and%20December%20of%20this%20year%20would%20be%20ineligible%20for%20refinancing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsumer%20protection%20advocates%20are%20are%20concerned%20that%20homebuyers%20are%20increasingly%20opting%20for%20non-traditional%20mortgages%20that%20carry%20higher%20risks.%20Some%20borrowers%20are%20attracted%20to%20interest-only%20loans%20by%20the%20lower%20monthly%20costs%2C%20but%20aren't%20prepared%20for%20worst-case%20scenarios%2C%20and%20to%20ultimately%20pay%20more%20to%20own%20their%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20question%20of%2C%20do%20people%20understand%20that%20this%20is%20a%20product%20that's%20going%20to%20be%20more%20expensive%20for%20them%20long%20term%2C%20or%20are%20they%20just%20enticed%20by%20the%20lower%20monthly%20payments%3F%26quot%3B%20B%C3%A4ckman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhenrys-risky-unusual-interest-only-mortgage-loan-home-prices-soar-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702726381000%2C%22visual