rbubble%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20in%20financial%20markets%2C%20and%20warned%20its%20popping%20would%20likely%20herald%20a%20harsh%20recession%2C%20during%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DcTvN9iFJ0fY%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20episode%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Great%20Simplification%26quot%3B%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20GMO%20cofounder%20and%20market%20historian%20touched%20on%20everything%20from%20his%20own%20net%20worth%20to%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20the%20need%20for%20Fed%20reform%2C%20housing%20affordability%2C%20income%20inequality%2C%20and%20the%20meme-stock%20craze%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHere%20are%20Grantham's%209%20best%20quotes%2C%20lightly%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity%3A%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20He%20got%20into%20finance%20for%20fun%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20got%20into%20finance%20for%20a%20very%20profound%20reason%2C%20and%20that%20was%20I%20asked%20which%20of%20my%20classmates%20from%20business%20school%20were%20having%20the%20most%20fun%3F%20Back%20then%20in%201968%2C%20by%20a%20very%20wide%20margin%2C%20the%20guys%20in%20the%20stock%20market%20were%20having%20the%20most%20fun.%20So%20I%20thought%2C%20'Well%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20miss%20out%20on%20that.'%20They%20were%20not%20only%20having%20more%20fun%2C%20but%20they%20were%20getting%20paid%20a%20hell%20of%20a%20lot%20more%20money.%20What's%20not%20to%20like%20about%20that%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20On%20not%20really%20being%20a%20billionaire%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20only%20a%20billionaire%20by%20a%20strange%20and%20generous%20construction%2C%20and%20that%20is%20if%20you%20count%20the%20money%20I%20have%20given%20away%2C%20which%20is%20a%20pretty%20whimsical%20way%20of%20calculating%20someone's%20net%20worth.%20But%20in%20terms%20of%20what%20I%20actually%20have%20and%20could%20go%20out%20and%20buy%20my%20daughter%20back%20from%20being%20kidnapped%20tomorrow%2C%20I'm%20at%20least%20an%20order%20of%20magnitude%20short%20of%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20On%20meme%20stocks%20in%202021%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%202021%2C%20we%20had%20utterly%20crazy%20behavior.%20I%20believe%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20scale%20of%20it%2C%20the%20biggest%2C%20most%20significant%20crazy%20behavior%20in%20recorded%20history%20of%20the%20US%20stock%20market.%26quot%3B%20(Grantham%20was%20referring%20to%20the%20mass%20hype%20and%20speculation%20around%20meme%20stocks%2C%20SPACs%2C%20crypto%2C%20NFTs%2C%20and%20other%20risky%20assets.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20On%20the%20risk%20of%20a%20superbubble%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuperbubbles%20go%20back%20to%20trend%20like%20all%20the%20normal%20bubbles%2C%20but%20they%20cause%20a%20whole%20lot%20more%20pain%20because%20they%20distort%20the%20system.%20When%20they%20inevitably%20break%2C%20they're%20always%20a%20shock%20because%20everyone%20has%20locked%20into%20the%20new%20paradigm.%20They%20eventually%20come%20down%20to%20trend%2C%20and%20all%20but%20one%20of%20them%20in%20history%20go%20below%20trend%20for%20a%20while%2C%20and%20that%20creates%20an%20enormous%20negative%20income%20effect%20and%20has%20always%20caused%20a%20recession.%26quot%3B%20(Grantham%C2%A0has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeremy-grantham-warns-us-stock-market-crash-downside-outlook-2023-12%5C%22%3Erepeatedly%20cautioned%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fgrantham-spx-stock-market-outlook-crash-house-prices-recession-bitcoin-2023-10%3Futm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_source%3Dmarkets%5C%22%3Ecrash%20by%20over%2050%25%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E5.%20The%20economy%20is%20in%20for%20a%20bad%20ride%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20miscalculate%2C%20the%20recession%20turns%20into%20something%20really%20terrible%20like%20the%20depression%20of%201929%2C%20like%20the%20bitter%20recession%20of%20the%20Nifty%2050%20in%20the%20'70s%2C%20or%20the%20near%20total%20financial%20collapse%20of%20the%20housing%20bust%20in%20'08.%20And%20one%20should%20expect%20something%20pretty%20bad%20this%20time.%20We%20await%20to%20see%20if%20this%20follows%20the%20pattern%20of%20history%2C%20or%20whether%20it%20is%20indeed%20that%20lovely%20creature%2C%20a%20new%20paradigm.%20But%20history%20is%20not%20kind%20to%20the%20new%20paradigm%20thinking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E6.%20America's%20income%20inequality%20is%20severe%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAn%20enlightened%20government%20will%20move%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20there%20is%20a%20fairly%20broad%2C%20acceptable%20income%C2%A0%20distribution.%20We%20are%20already%20falling%20foul%20of%20that.%20Our%20income%20distribution%20in%20the%20US%20is%20no%20longer%20passing%20that%20test.%20It%20has%20resulted%20in%20the%20estrangement%2C%20almost%20bitterness%20and%20anger%20of%20at%20least%20a%20third%20of%20the%20general%20public%20who%20feels%20they%20have%20been%20badly%20treated.%20I%20think%20you%20could%20make%20a%20pretty%20good%20case%20that%2C%20yes%2C%20they%20have%20been%20royally%20screwed%20since%20about%201975.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E7.%20There's%20good%20and%20bad%20capitalism%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20people%20who%20start%20their%20own%20darn%20firm%20like%20Mr.%20Musk%2C%20in%20a%20sense%20they%20deserve%20what%20they%20get.%20People%20who%20start%20a%20new%20enterprise%2C%20when%20you've%20paid%20all%C2%A0%20the%20rent%20and%20you've%20paid%20all%20the%20salaries%2C%20what's%20left%20is%20yours.%20I%20get%20that.%20That's%C2%A0%20capitalism.%20It's%20the%20best%20part%20of%20capitalism.%20When%20you%20put%20a%20bunch%20of%20your%20buddies%20on%20the%20board%2C%20and%20you%20decide%20to%20give%20yourself%20%24200%20million%20of%20stock%20options%20over%20three%20years%20because%20they're%20your%20friends%2C%20that%20isn't%20capitalism.%20That%20is%20stock-option%20culture%20gone%20wrong.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E8.%20Everything%20is%20unaffordable%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBuying%20a%20house%2C%20it's%20such%20a%20high%20unaffordability%20index%20now.%20Peak%20prices%20as%20a%20multiple%20of%20family%20income%20times%207.8%25%20mortgage%2C%20that%20is%20a%20brutal%20increase%20in%20your%20cost.%20So%20cars%2C%20houses%2C%20and%20real%20life%2C%20this%20is%20not%20a%20super%20comfortable%20world%20for%20everyone%20below%20halfway%20on%20the%20income%20scale.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E9.%20%C2%A0On%20the%20Fed%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20Fed%20has%20been%20given%20far%20too%20many%20responsibilities.%20If%20it%20was%20just%20responsible%20for%20making%20sure%20there%20was%20a%20decent%20amount%20of%20money%20available%C2%A0%20...%20but%20it's%20worried%20about%20inflation%2C%20about%20growth%2C%20about%20debt%2C%20unemployment.%20It's%20pretty%20well%20guaranteed%20it%20will%20settle%20for%20some%20simple%20policy%20of%20making%20rates%20cheap.%20Cheap%20rates%20were%20terrible%20for%20retirees%2C%20they%20were%20not%20getting%20paid%20anything.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrantham-stock-market-bubble-crash-recession-musk-housing-fed-speculation-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702726202000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657c6a1550edbc52a864b02f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fgrantham-stock-market-bubble-crash-recession-musk-housing-fed-speculation-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jeremy%20Grantham%20said%20the%20multi-asset%20bubble%20would%20likely%20burst%20and%20bring%20down%20the%20US%20economy%2C%20and%20lamented%20income%20inequality%20and%20unaffordable%20housing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tmohamed%40insider.com%20(Theron%20Mohamed)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.c