20further%20strengthen%20MI.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20a%20report%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fmumbai-indians-name-hardik-pandya-as-captain-for-ipl-2024-instead-of-rohit-sharma-9069835%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20claimed%20that%20Hardik%20Pandya%20laid%20down%20a%20condition%20for%20returning%20to%20Mumbai%20Indians%20from%20Gujarat%20Titans%2C%20where%20he%20was%20the%20skipper%20for%20two%20seasons%2C%20and%20that%20was%20he%20should%20be%20made%20the%20captain%20of%20the%20five-time%20IPL%20champions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20further%20claimed%20that%20Mumbai%20Indians%20management%20informed%20Rohit%20Sharma%20about%20their%20decision%20about%20Mumbai%20Indians%20captaincy%20change%20during%20the%20World%20Cup%202023.%20Rohit%20Sharma%20agreed%20to%20play%20under%20Hardik%20Pandya%20in%20the%20next%20IPL.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%2031%20matches%20for%20GT%20from%202022-23%2C%20Pandya%20scored%20833%20runs%20at%20an%20average%20of%2037.86%20and%20a%20strike%20rate%20of%20over%20133%2C%20with%20six%20half-centuries%20and%20a%20best%20score%20of%2087*.%20He%20also%20had%2011%20wickets%20for%20the%20team%2C%20with%20the%20best%20figures%20of%203%2F17.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPandya%20also%20played%2092%20matches%20for%20MI%20from%202015-2021%2C%20scoring%201%2C476%20runs%20at%20an%20average%20of%2027.33%20at%20a%20strike%20rate%20of%20over%20153%2C%20with%20four%20half-centuries%20and%20best%20score%20of%2091.%20He%20also%20took%2042%20wickets%20for%20the%20team%2C%20with%20the%20best%20bowling%20figures%20of%203%2F20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPandya%20has%20won%20five%20IPL%20trophies%2C%20four%20with%20MI%20(2015%2C%202017%2C%202019%2C%202020)%20and%20GT%20(2022).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702721520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fpq07akm_hardikpandya_640x480_28_November_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fipl-2024%2Fhardik-pandya-had-put-captaincy-condition-for-returning-to-mumbai-indians-report-4684857%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mumbai%20Indians%2C%20on%20Friday%2C%20officially%20confirmed%20that%20Hardik%20Pandya%20will%20lead%20them%20at%20the%20IPL%202024.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fipl-2024%2Fhardik-pandya-had-put-captaincy-condition-for-returning-to-mumbai-indians-report-4684857%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fipl-2024%2Fhardik-pandya-had-put-captaincy-condition-for-returning-to-mumbai-indians-report-4684857%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fipl-2024%2Fhardik-pandya-had-put-captaincy-condition-for-returning-to-mumbai-indians-report-4684857%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Explained%3A%20Key%20Events%20That%20Forced%2093%2C000%20Pak%20Troops%20To%20Surrender%20In%201971%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIndia%20celebrates%20Vijay%20Diwas%20today%20to%20mark%20the%20surrender%20of%20East%20Pakistan%20troops%20in%20the%201971%20war.%20Fifty-two%20years%20ago%20the%20war%20led%20to%20the%20liberation%20of%20East%20Pakistan%20and%20the%20creation%20of%20Bangladesh.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20important%20events%20played%20in%20India's%20favour%20that%20led%20to%20the%20fall%20of%20Pak%20regime%20in%20Dhaka%20and%20the%20surrender%20of%20over%2090%2C000%20troops%20in%20East%20Pakistan%20in%20a%20fortnight%20of%20fighting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ELand%2C%20Sea%20and%20Air%20Operation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEast%20Pakistan%20was%20isolated%20from%20its%20western%20half%20following%20India's%20declaration%20of%20a%20no-fly%20zone%20for%20Pakistani%20aeroplanes.%20A%20naval%20blockade%20in%20the%20west%20disrupted%20all%20routes%20to%20supply%20relief%20and%20ammunition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20three%20days%20of%20the%20start%20of%20the%20war%2C%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20established%20air%20superiority%20in%20East%20Pakistan%2C%20which%20helped%20in%20the%20swift%20advance%20of%20the%20army%20deep%20inside%20Bangladesh.%20INS%20Vikrant%2C%20the%20navy's%20aircraft%20carrier%2C%20and%20naval%20aviators%20blocked%20reinforcements%20to%20the%20east%2C%20cutting%20off%20escape%20routes%20and%20Sea%20Lines%20of%20Communication%20(SLOC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Indian%20Army's%204%2C%2033%20and%202%20Corps%20marched%20toward%20Bangladesh%20from%20three%20directions.%20The%20objective%20was%20to%20capture%20the%20%26quot%3Bfortress%20cities%26quot%3B%20built%20by%20Pakistani%20troops%20and%20move%20through%20the%20gaps%20to%20take%20on%20Dhaka.%20The%20fall%20of%20Sylhet%2C%20Chittagong%2C%20Tangail%2C%20Khulna%2C%20Jessore%2C%20etc.%20ensured%20no%20escape%20route%20was%20left.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EPsychological%20Warfare%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20war%20began%2C%20the%20Pakistani%20troops%20in%20the%20east%20led%20by%20General%20AAK%20Niazi%20believed%20that%20India%20would%20take%20territories%20along%20the%20border%20in%20West%20Bengal.%20This%20false%20impression%20forced%20Pakistan%20to%20create%20%26quot%3Bfortress%20cities%26quot%3B%20around%20Dhaka%2C%20leaving%20insufficient%20troops%20in%20the%20capital.%20The%20fall%20of%20each%20city%20made%20Dhaka%20look%20closer%20and%20air%20dropping%20in%20Tangail%2C%20which%20was%20reported%20as%20a%20paradrop%20of%205%2C000%20troops%2C%20was%20a%20psychological%20blow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20army%20chief%20General%20Sam%20Manekshaw%20(later%20Field%20Marshal)%20broadcast%20a%20message%20for%20Pakistani%20troops%20after%20the%20fall%20of%20Jessore%20on%20December%208%2C%20warning%20Pakistani%20troops%20and%20assuring%20them%20%26quot%3BOnce%20you%20surrender%2C%20you%20shall%20be%20treated%20with%20dignity%20as%20per%20Geneva%20Convention%26quot%3B.%20On%20December%2010%2C%20in%20another%20message%2C%20General%20Manekshaw%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYour%20resistance%20is%20gallant%20but%20fruitless...Your%20commanders%20are%20giving%20false%20hopes.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EUS%2C%20China%20Fail%20To%20Come%20To%20The%20Rescue%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELt%20Gen%20Niazi%20reportedly%20told%20Maj%20General%20JFR%20Jacob%20after%20the%20surrender%20that%20he%20had%20recognised%20defeat%20at%20least%20seven%20days%20before%20the%20troops%20gave%20up%20arms.%20Pakistan%20had%20pinned%20its%20hopes%20on%20the%20US%20and%20China.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20support%20from%20the%20USSR%20prompted%20Pakistan%20to%20seek%20help%20from%20the%20US%20during%20the%20Cold%20War.%20The%20Chinese%20were%20recovering%20from%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20'Cultural%20Revolution'%20and%20a%20war%20deep%20inside%20India%20did%20not%20favour%20them.%20Massive%20mobilization%20of%20Chinese%20troops%20in%20winter%20had%20to%20be%20carried%20out%20to%20penetrate%20deep%20inside%20East%20Pakistan%20and%20ensure%20supply%20lines%20were%20maintained.%C2%A0For%20China%2C%20diverting%20Indian%20troops%20to%20the%20northeast%20meant%20going%20for%20a%20high-altitude%20winter%20war.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20US%20President%20Richard%20Nixon%20ordered%20the%20deployment%20of%20its%20Seventh%20Fleet%20comprising%20its%20nuclear-powered%20aircraft%20carrier%20-%20USS%20Enterprise.%20President%20Nixon%20believed%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20US%20fleet%20would%20take%20on%20INS%20Vikrant%2C%20weaken%20India's%20naval%20blockade%20and%20force%20the%20navy%20to%20step%20back%20on%20the%20defensive%20because%20of%20the%20US'%20%26quot%3BGunboat%20Diplomacy%26quot%3B.%20The%20Indo-Soviet%20treaty%20came%20to%20the%20rescue.%20USSR%20deployed%20frigates%2C%20cruisers%2C%20tankers%20and%20destroyers%20armed%20with%20atomic%20missiles.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20deployment%20brought%20the%20two%20superpowers%20against%20each%20other%20and%20hostilities%20were%20defused%2C%20leaving%20Pakistan%20in%20the%20east%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ESurrender%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERapid%20Indian%20advance%20coupled%20with%20joint%20air%20and%20naval%20operations%20broke%20the%20supply%20of%20any%20help%20to%20East%20Pakistan.%20In%20the%20Western%20theatre%2C%20Pakistani%20troops%20managed%20to%20resist%20strongly%2C%20and%20the%20Pakistan%20Air%20Force%20provided%20air%20support%20to%20its%20troops%2C%20but%20in%20the%20east%2C%20the%20fall%20of%20Dhaka%20was%20inevitable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20December%2013%2C%20Gen%20Niazi%20sent%20a%20distress%20signal%20to%20Rawalpindi%20in%20West%20Pakistan%20but%20was%20told%20to%20continue%20fighting%20and%20hold%20as%20much%20territory%20as%20possible.%20A%20day%20later%2C%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20bombed%20the%20Governor%20House%20in%20Dhaka%20when%20a%20meeting%20was%20ongoing%20in%20the%20building.%20The%20air%20strike%20had%20such%20a%20demoralizing%20effect%20that%20the%20East%20Pakistan%20government%20resigned%20on%20the%20spot.%20This%20was%20the%20last%20straw%20on%20the%20camel's%20back%20and%20Niazi%20chose%20peace%20over%20more%20fighting.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702721340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2F7nera9b_vijaw-diwas-_625x300_16_December_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fexplained-key-factors-that-forced-93-000-pak-troops-to-surrender-in-1971-4684760%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20celebrates%20Vijay%20Diwas%20today%20to%20mark%20the%20surrender%20of%20East%20Pakistan%20troops%20in%20the%201971%20war.%20Fifty-two%20years%20ago%20the%20war%20led%20to%20the%20liberation%20of%20East%20Pakistan%20and%20the%20creation%20of%20Bangladesh.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fexplained-key-factors-that-forced-93-000-pak-troop