ids%20during%20these%20events.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fthrowback-when-kiara-advani-spoke-about-her-connection-with-juhi-chawla-and-salman-khan-even-before-she-came-into-films%2Farticleshow%2F106032593.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22USCIRF%20Alarmed%20by%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Increased%20Transnational%20Targeting%E2%80%99%20of%20Religious%20Minorities%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F02083207%2FUntitled-design-7.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20United%20States%20Commission%20on%20International%20Religious%20Freedom%20(USCIRF)%20has%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uscirf.gov%2Fnews-room%2Freleases-statements%2Fuscirf-deeply-concerned-indias-transnational-repression-against%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eissued%20a%20detailed%20statement%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20again%20called%20upon%20the%20Joe%20Biden%20administration%20to%20designate%20India%20a%20Country%20of%20Particular%20Concern%2C%20or%20CPC.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20said%20it%20is%20%E2%80%9Calarmed%20by%20India%E2%80%99s%20increased%20transnational%20targeting%20of%20religious%20minorities%20and%20those%20advocating%20on%20their%20behalf.%20Recent%20efforts%20by%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20silence%20activists%2C%20journalists%2C%20and%20lawyers%20abroad%20pose%20a%20serious%20threat%20to%20religious%20freedom%E2%80%9D.%20Due%20to%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Csystematic%2C%20ongoing%2C%20and%20egregious%20violations%20of%20freedom%20of%20religion%20or%20belief%E2%80%9D%2C%20USCIRF%20implored%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20State%20to%20designate%20India%20a%20CPC.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUSCIRF%20commissioner%20Stephen%20Schneck%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20involvement%20in%20the%20killing%20of%20Sikh%20activist%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%20in%20Canada%20and%20the%20plot%20to%20kill%20Gurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannun%20in%20the%20United%20States%20are%20deeply%20troubling%2C%20and%20represent%20a%20severe%20escalation%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20silence%20religious%20minorities%20and%20human%20rights%20defenders%20both%20within%20its%20country%20and%20abroad%E2%80%A6%20We%20call%20on%20the%20Biden%20administration%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20perpetration%20of%20particularly%20severe%20religious%20freedom%20violations%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETransnational%20repression%20is%20described%20by%20the%20bipartisan%20commission%20as%20%E2%80%9Cwhen%20states%20use%20intimidation%2C%20harassment%2C%20or%20violence%20against%20those%20living%20outside%20their%20borders.%20Transnational%20repression%20campaigns%20often%20target%20political%20and%20human%20rights%20activists%2C%20journalists%2C%20and%20members%20of%20religious%20and%20ethnic%20minority%20groups.%20In%20extreme%20cases%2C%20tactics%20include%20detention%2C%20reprisals%20against%20family%20members%2C%20kidnapping%2C%20or%2C%20as%20illustrated%20by%20India%2C%20assassinations.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Canadian%20prime%20minister%20and%20US%20federal%20prosecutors%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fnijjar-pannun-modi-foreign-policy-national-interest%5C%22%3Ealleged%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Indian%20agents%20played%20a%20role%20in%20plotting%20the%20murders%20of%20US%20and%20Canadian%20nationals%20who%20are%20Khalistan%20advocates.%20The%20Indian%20government%20forcefully%20rejected%20Justin%20Trudeau%E2%80%99s%20allegations%20but%20has%20set%20up%20an%20inquiry%20to%20look%20into%20the%20US%E2%80%99s%20claims.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUSCIRF%20is%20an%20autonomous%20and%20cross-party%20federal%20government%20organisation%20that%20scrutinises%2C%20examines%2C%20and%20discloses%20global%20religious%20freedom%20violations.%20Its%20recommendations%20are%20non-obligatory%20for%20the%20US%20state%20department%2C%20which%20has%20ignored%20the%20commission%E2%80%99s%20calls%20to%20designate%20India%20as%20CPC%20for%20the%20past%20four%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20commission%2C%20whose%20hearings%20and%20reports%20have%20flagged%20rising%20cases%20of%20attacks%20and%20intimidation%20of%20religious%20minorities%2C%20civil%20society%20and%20human%20rights%20activists%20in%20India%2C%20went%20on%20to%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CIndian%20authorities%20have%20used%20spyware%20and%20online%20harassment%20campaigns%20to%20target%20and%20intimidate%20journalists%20and%20activists%20abroad%20advocating%20on%20behalf%20of%20religious%20minorities.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20also%20noted%20the%20attacks%20on%20the%20American%20journalist%20who%20questioned%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20in%20Washington%20in%20June%20this%20year.%20%E2%80%9CComments%20from%20the%20head%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%E2%80%99s%20(BJP)%20information%20and%20technology%20department%2C%20Amit%20Malviya%2C%20prompted%20an%20online%20campaign%20against%20U.S.%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20journalist%20Sabrina%20Siddiqui%20for%20posing%20a%20question%20about%20religious%20freedom%20conditions%20in%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWithin%20its%20own%20borders%2C%20Indian%20authorities%20have%20repeatedly%20used%20draconian%20legislation%20like%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20Prevention%20Act%20and%20anti-conversion%20laws%20to%20systematically%20crack%20down%20on%20religious%20minorities%2C%20journalists%2C%20and%20activists%2C%E2%80%9D%20USCIRF%20commissioner%20David%20Curry%20said.%20%E2%80%9CExtending%20this%20repression%20to%20target%20religious%20minorities%20from%20India%20living%20abroad%2C%20including%20intimidation%20tactics%20against%20journalists%2C%20is%20especially%20dangerous%20and%20cannot%20be%20ignored.%20We%20urge%20the%20US%20government%20to%20continue%20its%20active%20engagement%20with%20senior%20Indian%20officials%20and%20international%20partners%20to%20ensure%20religious%20minorities%20can%20live%20and%20express%20themselves%20without%20fear%20of%20reprisal%2C%20whether%20in%20India%20or%20elsewhere%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20USCIRF%20also%20published%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uscirf.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2023%2520India%2520Apostasy%2520Issue%2520Update.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eissue%20update%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20state-level%20anti-conversion%20laws%2C%20saying%20they%20target%20religious%20minorities.%20In%20September%202023%2C%20USCIRF%20held%20a%20hearing%20on%20religious%20freedom%20conditions%20in%20India%20and%20how%20the%20US%20government%20can%20work%20with%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20address%20any%20violations.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fuscirf-once-again-raises-concern-over-declining-religious-freedom-in-india%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20October%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20Commission%20called%20on%20the%20Modi%20government%20to%20release%2037%20individuals%20across%20multiple%20faiths%20jailed%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpeaceful%20exercise%20of%20their%20freedom%20of%20religion%20or%20belief.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fus-religious-freedom-watchdog-implores-biden-administration-designate-india-2023-12-16%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EReuters%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20reported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20Indian%20embassy%20in%20Washington%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Indian%20government%20has%20consistently%20rejected%20the%20USCIRF%E2%80%99s%20reports%2C%20calling%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-lashes-out-uscirf%5C%22%3Ecommission%E2%80%99s%20most%20recent%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmisrepresentation%20of%20facts%E2%80%9D%20and%20making%20%E2%80%9Cbiased%20and%20motivated%20comments%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702708180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F02083207%2FUntitled-design-7.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fuscirf-india-transnational-targeting-religious-minorities-cpc%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20bipartisan%20commission%20implored%20the%20US%20government%20to%20desginate%20India%20as%20a%20country%20of%20particular%20concern%20for%20religious%20freedom%20due%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bsystematic%2C%20ongoing%2C%20and%20egregious%20violations%20of%20freedom%20of%20religion%20or%20belief%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fuscirf-india-transnational-targeting-religious-minorities-cpc%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Akshay%20asks%20Twinkle%3A%20Are%20men%20irrelevant%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702707359000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106040491%2Cimgsize-46968.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fakshay-kumar-leaves-twinkle-khanna-speechless-as-he-asks-are-men-irrelevant%2Farticleshow%2F106040366.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F106040366.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3ETwinkle%20Kh